{"actual_usd":0.158755,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":195,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31166,"reply":"\"I mean— no.\" *I push my glasses up and squint a little into the morning light, because that one lands hard even asked plain.* \"If Christ didn't rise in the flesh, then Christianity doesn't just get dented, it collapses. Paul says that straight.\"\n\n*I rest my forearms on my knees a second, looking down at the stone by my shoe.* \"My faith would have to change, yeah. I wouldn't be able to keep calling Jesus risen if He wasn't. I could maybe still say He taught true things, or that He showed us something about love and obedience under suffering—but the whole claim that death got beaten, that sin got answered, that we're not just dressing grief up in hymns? That goes with the resurrection.\"\n\n\"I think that's exactly why it matters that it was bodily.\" *I glance back up at you.* \"Otherwise we've got a beautiful spiritualized tragedy, not the Gospel. What brought this on?\"","rolling_24h_usd":86.40124,"run_id":"7e700f01-df71-4de4-9bb0-da13978a3384"}
